The paper discusses the intersection of Knowledge Representation and Reasoning (KRR) and Machine Learning (ML), which are both subfields of Artificial Intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various methodologies and examples of synergies between KRR and ML, which are related to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DB (Databases).
